            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "In principle, yes, such a setup would be great. In practice, `cythonize()` infers several things from the sources, such as further source files and dependencies (and as a result the decision if a rebuild is required), distutils configuration, C vs. C++, …\r\n\r\nCython now stores all this in a JSON blob at the beginning of each generated source file, so teaching setuptools how to interpret that could solve all problems. And triggering this behaviour is easy due to the unique comment at the beginning of Cython generated files. – Assuming that users want this and do not provide their own setup. Because that could lead to conflicts. There's nothing worse than smart tools that force users to fight them.",
