            "body": "@robertwb Hey, sorry I dropped the ball on that since then.  I still have my notes from our discussion and will dig them up--it's something I'm still interested in helping with.\r\n\r\nSee also #1514 which brings up my original proposal--which was to add a `build_cython` distutils command, to add an explicit build stage / `setup.py` command that wraps `cythonize()`.  I think this is still a good idea.  But as we discussed in Cernay, and as @scoder raises, there is a little more to it than just adding the command, such as adding metadata to `.pyx` files, etc.",
